B(x,r)
\mathbb R^{\omega}
x = (1,1/2,1/3,\ldots)
g
  B(x,r) = \{ y = (y_i) : |x_i - y_i| < r \mbox{ for all }i \}         = \prod_{i=1}^{\infty} B(x_i, r) = \prod_{i=1}^{\infty} (x_i - r, x_i + r) 
  B(x, 1) = \prod_{i=1}^{\infty} \left( \frac{1}{n} - 1, \frac{1}{n} + 1 \right) 
  g^{-1}(B(x,1)) = \bigcap_{i=1}^{\infty} \left( \frac{1}{n} - 1, \frac{1}{n} + 1 \right) = (0,1] 
B(x,r)
y = (1, 1/2, 1/3, \dots)
z := (1, 1, 1, \dots) \in B(y, 1)
B(z, \epsilon) \not \subset B(y, 1)
\epsilon > 0
